      "source": [
        "### 1.4 Translation matrix\n",
        "\n",
        "Translation is a transformation that moves every point of a figure by a fixed distance.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "![Image 3.png](data:image/png;base64,)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "YqtNveE7nmCm"
      },
      "source": [
        "Here, you should build a translation matrix and apply translation by $(20, 25)$ to the vector. Start from explaining how to construct a translation matrix:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "jhFCp68crzxt"
      },
      "source": [
        "*(Your answer goes here)*\n",
        "\n",
        "For translation matrix we cant use 2x2 matrix no more, because it can just rotate or shear around itself, (e. g. just scale its coordinates)\n",
        "So to move every point, we need to use 3x3 matrix, where there will be the third column, that will take constants, by which we can move our matrix\n",
        "\n",
        "$ \n",
        " A \\begin{pmatrix} x \\\\ y \\\\1 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 & t1 \\\\ 0 & 1 & t2 \\\\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\end{pmatrix} \\begin{pmatrix} x \\\\ y \\\\ 1 \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} x + t1 \\\\ y + t2 \\\\ 1 \\end{pmatrix}\n",
        "$\n",
        "This way it wouldnt scale or rotate itself, just add the constants t1 and t2\n",
        "\n",
        "So, in our case, A should be:\n",
        "$\n",
        "\\begin{pmatrix} 1 & 0 & 20 \\\\ 0 & 1 & 25 \\\\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\end{pmatrix}\n",
        "$\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "nzGwDQyR-mge"
      },
      "source": [
        "Then, implement a function that produces such a matrix:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 11,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "y2k0f6IuA6Yb"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Translation matrix is\n",
            "[[ 1  0 20]\n",
            " [ 0  1 25]\n",
            " [ 0  0  1]]\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "##### YOUR CODE STARTS #####\n",
        "def get_translation_matrix(translation_factor_x, translation_factor_y):\n",
        "  return np.array([[1, 0, translation_factor_x], [0 , 1, translation_factor_y], [0, 0, 1]])\n",
        "\n",
        "M4 = get_translation_matrix(20, 25)\n",
        "##### YOUR CODE ENDS #####\n",
        "print(\"Translation matrix is\")\n",
        "print(M4)"
      ]
    },
