      "source": [
        "### 1.5 Rotation matrix\n",
        "\n",
        "Rotation is a linear transformation of some space that preserves at least one point. An example of rotation by angle $\\psi$ on xy-plane is depicted on the image below:   \n",
        "![Image 1.png](data:image/png;base64,)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "VaYJnGxXFtZi"
      },
      "source": [
        "Derive the transformation matrix that corresponds to rotation by a generic angle $\\phi$?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ei8JHzw2FtZi"
      },
      "source": [
        "*(Your answer is here)*\n",
        "\n",
        "To rotate a point $(x, y)$ by angle $\\phi$, we look at what happens to the two basis vectors.\n",
        "\n",
        "When we rotate $(1, 0)$ by $\\phi$, it is on $(cos(\\phi), sin(\\phi))$.\n",
        "When we rotate $(0, 1)$ by $\\phi$, it is on $(-sin(\\phi), cos(\\phi))$.\n",
        "\n",
        "Placing these as columns of our matrix:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$A \\begin{pmatrix} x \\\\ y \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} cos(\\phi) & -sin(\\phi) \\\\ sin(\\phi) & cos(\\phi) \\end{pmatrix} \\begin{pmatrix} x \\\\ y \\end{pmatrix} = \\begin{pmatrix} x \\cdot cos(\\phi) - y \\cdot sin(\\phi) \\\\ x \\cdot sin(\\phi) + y \\cdot cos(\\phi) \\end{pmatrix}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "So, our A is:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$\\begin{pmatrix} cos(\\phi) & -sin(\\phi) \\\\ sin(\\phi) & cos(\\phi) \\end{pmatrix}$$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "lYreDKZPFtZi"
      },
      "source": [
        "Your next task is to implement a function that calculates the rotation matrix and apply it to a vector to rotate it by $45^\\circ$.\n",
        "First, construct the rotation matrix:"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 15,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Vjt2GjkAFtZi"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Rotation matrix is\n",
            "[[ 0.70710678 -0.70710678]\n",
            " [ 0.70710678  0.70710678]]\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Create rotation matrix\n",
        "\n",
        "def get_rotation_matrix(phi):\n",
        "  ##### YOUR CODE STARTS #####\n",
        "  transformation_matrix = np.array([\n",
        "        [np.cos(np.radians(phi)), -np.sin(np.radians(phi))],\n",
        "        [np.sin(np.radians(phi)),  np.cos(np.radians(phi))]\n",
        "    ])\n",
        "  ##### YOUR CODE ENDS #####\n",
        "  return transformation_matrix\n",
        "\n",
        "phi = 45\n",
        "M = get_rotation_matrix(phi)\n",
        "print(\"Rotation matrix is\")\n",
        "print(M)"
      ]
    },
