      "source": [
        "The outputs don't really coincide. They look slightly different because the order of transformations changes the result.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Is it possible to obtain same/different result changing the order of transformations?**\n",
        "\n",
        "Yes, depending on which transformations to do.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Different result: when $AB \\neq BA$, for example translation and scaling in our case\n",
        "\n",
        "- Same result: when $AB = BA$, for example two rotations by angles $\\alpha$ and $\\beta$ \n",
        "always give the same result regardless of order:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$R_\\alpha R_\\beta = R_\\beta R_\\alpha = R_{\\alpha+\\beta}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "**Theoretical derivation:**\n",
        "\n",
        "$$S = \\begin{bmatrix} 1.5 & 0 & 0 \\\\ 0 & 2 & 0 \\\\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\end{bmatrix}, \\quad R = \\begin{bmatrix} \\cos\\theta & -\\sin\\theta & 0 \\\\ \\sin\\theta & \\cos\\theta & 0 \\\\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\end{bmatrix}, \\quad T = \\begin{bmatrix} 1 & 0 & t_x \\\\ 0 & 1 & t_y \\\\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\end{bmatrix}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "$T$ and $S$ do not satisfy $TS = ST$:\n",
        "\n",
        "$$TS = \\begin{bmatrix} 1.5 & 0 & t_x \\\\ 0 & 2 & t_y \\\\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\end{bmatrix}, \\quad ST = \\begin{bmatrix} 1.5 & 0 & 1.5t_x \\\\ 0 & 2 & 2t_y \\\\ 0 & 0 & 1 \\end{bmatrix}$$\n",
        "\n",
        "Since $t_x \\neq 1.5 t_x$ and $t_y \\neq 2t_y$, we have $TS \\neq ST$, which proves that the order of transformations matters and the two compositions produce different results."
      ]
    },
